Re-Building a Modern Portfolio
Quick: what=E2=80=99s the best way to structure your investment portfolio?
For the past few decades, the answer has been easy: the 60/40 portfolio. Pu=
t 60% in equities, 40% in bonds and call it a day.=C2=A0
That approach is easy to understand. 60% of your money should appreciate an=
d grow, and 40% should generate income. Buy some index funds, buy some trea=
suries, call it a day. It=E2=80=99s also, unfortunately, the wrong approach=
 today.=C2=A0
Why? There are a few reasons.=C2=A0
Interest rates are super low.
